    <section id="the-spreadsheet-trap">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">The Spreadsheet Trap: Why Your Excel Estimator is a Scaling Liability</h2>
      <p>
        Every home builder has a "Mega-Sheet." It's the file everyone relies on, but only one person truly understands. This is the <strong>Key-Man Risk</strong> that stalls growth. If your master estimator is out for a week, does your bidding process grind to a halt?
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">The "Takeoff Error" Tax</h3>
      <p>
        A single broken formula in a cell can result in a $15,000 margin erosion on a single custom home. These aren't just errors; they are a tax on your business. Manual data entry into spreadsheets is inherently prone to human failure. When you multiply this by thirty active bids, the probability of a "silent killer" error reaching the contract stage approaches 100%.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Version Control Hell</h3>
      <p>
        "Estimator_Final_v2_REVISED_JAN.xlsx" is not a version control system. When material prices for copper or lumber spike on Tuesday, how long does it take to update every active bid? In a spreadsheet-heavy environment, the answer is usually "too long," leading to bids based on yesterday's costs in today's market.
      </p>

