      <p>
        Many residential builders still rely on "Cost Per Square Foot" as their primary house construction estimator logic. While useful for high-level feasibility, it's a dangerous way to run a business. Scaling requires <strong>Assembly Pricing</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Instead of counting individual studs, nails, and labor hours for every wall, a custom software solution treats a "Framed Wall" as a single atomic assembly. When you draw a line or enter a dimension, the software automatically calculates the entire <strong>Bill of Materials (BOM)</strong> and labor burden associated with that assembly.
      </p>
